Doing an experiment in real life is usually not a good idea and it  could backfire easily. First of all, because experiments are supposed to be a test on whether some ideas work and, second of all, the outcome could be unpredictable and spiral out of control. That’s why a simulation is usually preferred, because it’s cost-effective and easier to manage. For example, the company is calculating how many employees they need for the current workload. They can’t just hire people and then when they need less people, fire someone. This could lead to some consequences, that’s why simulation is introduced. It improves the quality of life for the customers and company.